<h2>Color</h2>

<p>WebBlocks provides a consistent and robust color implementation. By consistent, any color class described by this module may be applied in any context. One can just as easily apply a color onto a <code>td</code>, <code>div</code>, <code>button</code> or anything else, and they may do so as the text color or the background color. By robust, this implementation allows one to customize the behavior of a color in all its contexts by tweaking a single hex value, modifying shader and contrast values or even defining each aspect of a color directly.</p>

<p>This library includes a large number of modules related to color. Generally, colors are included as a single module <code>Base/Color</code>, and many entities include them as a requisite.</p>

