<h3>Color Classifications</h3>

<h4>Color Sets</h4>

<p>WebBlocks defines two color sets</p>

<ul>
    <li><strong>Branding colors</strong> denote a marketing element</li>
    <li><strong>Mood colors</strong> denote the sentiment of an element</li>
</ul>

<h4>Branding Color Set</h4>

<p>The branding color classes are:</p>

<ul>
    <li><span class="badge primary">.primary</span></li>
    <li><span class="badge secondary">.secondary</span></li>
    <li><span class="badge tertiary">.tertiary</span></li>
    <li><span class="badge neutral">.neutral</span></li>
    <li><span class="badge default">.default</span></li>
</ul>

<h4>Mood Color Set</h4>

<p>The mood color classes are:</p>

<ul>
    <li><span class="badge info">.info</span></li>
    <li><span class="badge success">.success</span></li>
    <li><span class="badge warning">.warning</span></li>
    <li><span class="badge error">.error</span></li>
    <li><span class="badge danger">.danger</span></li>
    <li><span class="badge important">.important</span></li>
    <li><span class="badge inverse">.inverse</span></li>
    <li><span class="badge required">.required</span></li>
    <li><span class="badge highlight">.highlight</span></li>
</ul>

<h4>Color Flavors</h4>

<p>WebBlocks provides two classes that may be used to flavor a color:</p>

<ul>
    <li><code>.gradient</code> adds a gradient to the color such as <span class="badge primary gradient">.primary.gradient</span></li>
    <li><code>.light</code> uses a light variant of the color such as <span class="badge primary light">.primary.light</span></li>
    <li><code>.light.gradient</code> uses a light gradient variant of the color such as <span class="badge primary light gradient">.primary.light.gradient</span></li>
    <li><code>.dark</code> uses a dark variant of the color such as <span class="badge primary dark">.primary.dark</span></li>
    <li><code>.dark.gradient</code> uses a dark gradient variant of the color such as <span class="badge primary dark gradient">.primary.light.gradient</span></li>
</ul>

<h4>Text Colors</h4>

<p>WebBlocks also provides a set of text colors by prepending <code>text-</code> on a branding or mood class:</p>
